ph of Truth</span><hr size=1> The same political upheaval which brought many fine trolls to see the greater good of balance last eve led to a bloody but decisive battle in Innothule.<br>
<br>
As I traveled with my friends Oogpik, Faellen, Dreadknot, Vorasious, Illuminaty, Lolanthe we thought to do battle with the frogs to rest yet another stolen artifact which rightfully belonged to humans. Little did I know or understand that before the night was out I would be fighting at the side of those same frogs to save human lives.<br>
<br>
An evil had arisen in Grobb and the trolls of Grobb sought to bring down the last temple of Mithanial Marr. This battle would pit brother and guild mate against each other in the confusion. <br>
<br>
Imagine my surprise when we encountered the first pitched battle in Innothule and I heard from teh croacking mouths of what I now know to be a paladin froglok the battle of cry of Marr.<br>
<br>
The frogs were there to stop the trolls from their intent to destroy Freeport and with it the temple. Our dark elf enchanter Illuminaty and troll Oogpik guildmates strove to remain neutral in the conflict, but in the end blood alliances must remain strong. As we drove the trolls back to Grobb it became obvious that the frogloks would not be appeased by this retreat and would not rest till the evil that had driven the trolls to war was put down.<br>
<br>
Those who serve Marr and the goodness of Tunare followed. But Oogpik could not bear to see his home routed and went to defend kith and kin and Illuminaty intent to protect his friend and guild brother went with him. The pain of realizing we would parted brothers but would soon meet as enemies tore at my heart. But my love of marr and the truth sent me to volunteer in the camp of the Frogloks. I wept as I saw my old friends fall in battle, and Shariona true to her calling, heedless trying to save new ally and friend alike both pitched herself into the fray.<br>
<br>
In the end Oogpik limped from the defeated city and we welcome him now homeless back into our guild hall. The noble paladins of the Frogloks now control Grobb it has been renamed Gupt, and is now an outpost of Marr to his greater glory and Truth.<br>
<br>
I beg that all of us remember in the aftermath of this bloody battle, that we were guildmates before, and still. No matter what side was chosen by blood and clan allegiance, we are still brothers. Please put aside those blood feuds and reclaim your guildmates and friends, let us claim peace.<br>
<br>
To those who may be concerned about the trolls refugees driven from their swamp, I understand that the Dark Elves have honored their alliance with the trolls and provided refuge to those driven from their homes by this devastating battle. <br>
<br>
May Marr preserve the new outpost and the brave Frogloks who now stand against teh darkness.<br>
Toric Seerson<br>
Venerable Elder<br>
